<?xml version="1.0"?>
<rdf:RDF xmlns="http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/pe#"
     xml:base="http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/pe"
     xmlns:pe="http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/pe#"
     xmlns:owl="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#"
     xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#"
     xmlns:xml="http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace"
     xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#"
     xmlns:foaf="http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/"
     xmlns:rdfs="http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#"
     xmlns:skos="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#"
     xmlns:tbox="http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox#">
    <owl:Ontology rdf:about="http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/pe">
        <owl:imports rdf:resource="http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox"/>
        <profilingPolicy xml:lang="en">
Programming-language profiling uses only native support and standard-library support.
Refined concepts are asserted selectively rather than exhaustively.
No support is recorded for mere encodings or otherwise insignificant realizations.
Refined support is not inherited automatically from coarse support.
Support assertions are qualified only when especially representative or potentially ambiguous.
Borderline cases may be documented using skos:note.
Paradigm-based subclassing of programming languages is not used; paradigms are represented via concept support.
</profilingPolicy>
        <tbox:commentingPolicy xml:lang="en">See http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox -- the same policy applies here.</tbox:commentingPolicy>
        <tbox:formattingPolicy xml:lang="en">See http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox -- the same policy applies here.</tbox:formattingPolicy>
        <tbox:linkingPolicy xml:lang="en">See http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox -- the same policy applies here.</tbox:linkingPolicy>
        <tbox:metamodelingPolicy xml:lang="en">See http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox -- the same policy applies here.</tbox:metamodelingPolicy>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Sub-ontology / ABox for programming-language concepts and programming languages</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Ontology>
    


